  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Challenges Men Having Sex with Men (MSM) Face in Accessing Minimum Prevention Package Intervention (MPPI)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">For the sustenance of peer led HIV prevention MSM intervention; identifying challenges through operational research that MSM community members face while accessing HIV prevention services and impediments experienced by service providers in reaching MSM with HIV prevention services will create opportunities for gaps to be addressed from an evidenced informed standpoint. This will improve access and uptake of prevention services by MSM thereby causing an increase in knowledge of HIV transmission and acquisition routes, build skills (condom negotiation and assertiveness), promote risk reduction activities and increase access to HCT and STI services.  The ultimate goal is to facilitate a reduction in new infections among MSM.</narrative>
  </description>
